Sorry, forgot to add: Do not let the sauce boil or even simmer, just heat to steaming and then remove from burner. Curdling can also result from too high a temp.

Rating: 3
An excellent pasta dish - like spring on a plate! Make it often and it is always delicious and enjoyed by all. Suggestion to those cooks who reported curdled sauce: Try adding the lemon juice/zest directly to the cold milk or cream before heating rather than adding it later as the recipe directs. Was told by a professional cook many years ago that when milk/cream is heated the structure of the protein in the milk solids changes, so the addition of the lemon then is almost certain to curdle the sauce. Have been following this method ever since with great success. Hope you find this tip helpful. Enjoy!

