A couple of suggestions for the fellow members. 1. - Grilled asparagus make it more intense flavour. To grill them easily place 4-5 on 2 skewers; one near the tips and one at the bottom, drizzle with olive oil before grilling. 2. - Use the same pot where you cooked the pasta, return the drain pasta into it and add the sauce, cook at VERY low heat for a minute or so COVERED, serve with the grilled and cut asparagus on top. The lemon intensity can be adjusted to taste when making the sauce. Garlic does add another dimension to this dish, capers can also be added. ENJOY!

