Simply superb! This is one of my favourite pasta dishes and it never fails to please. It can be easily adapted: try adding sauteed shrimp or scallops, finely grated parmesan and garlic to the sauce, a few sliced green onions, a generous amount of fresh minced dill, lots of fresh ground pepper, or snow peas instead of asparagus - all are excellent variations! I never add the pasta water to the sauce (WHY do that?), sometimes use half and half and always reduce the butter amount with no appreciable loss of flavour or richness. I have found the juice and zest from one large lemon is just right, otherwise it is too acidic/tangy and the lemon overpowers the other delicate flavours. Very company pleasing with much eye appeal and a delight to serve and eat! A true winner!

