Rating: 3
I think the varying responses might be due both to personal taste AND the lemons purchased... some lemons are more acidid than others and the intensity of the lemon peel can vary, too, I've found. I have made this dish (as have friends) successfully a number of times and found that if you start with only a tablespoon of lemon peel and about an 1/8th cup of lemon juice you are better off. stick a piece of bread into the sauce and test it before adding more, just in case the lemons you've purchased pack a punch! I tend to prefer it with a cup of half/half rather than the cream/water combination... a bit less 'greasy' tasting to those of us who eat lower fat most of the time... and I also find that you really need the pepper to balance the lemon... don't skimp! Chicken sauteed in the butter and cut into big chunks (6-8 per chicken breast half) add a lovely color and also make this dish more hearty for those who want their protein! I love this dish and it's been a part of my repertoire for a long time :) The only caution is to go carefully with the lemon. "Too much" can vary by the lemons purchased, and spoil a perfect meal. Bon apetit!

